attributes.Long form description: The student is taking apart a rolling cart. He removes the wheels, then the bolts holding on the shelves, and finally the sidebars and base frame.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles all four wheels from the furniture.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: Student should not drop the wrench.

attributes.Action sentence: The student unscrews the two bolts of the middle tray and one bolt of the top tray.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The shelf needs to be laying down.

attributes.Transcription: You should keep the structure laying down the side *unintelligible*.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the middle tray.
The student disassembles the top tray.
The student disassembles the bottom tray.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: Student should place the structure in a stand-up position first.

attributes.Transcription: You should put the structure, uh, standing up again to remove the last basket.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the side bars of the rolling cart.
The student disassembles all the legs.

attributes.Transcription: You can press the stop button.
